clip_title: My humble life is in debt to your exalted prowess
transcript:
Gilbert of Glockenspur:
My humble life is indebted to your exalted prowess, your dauntless courage, and your superb, swift sword! 
Bowen:
You have the poet's gift of exaggeration. 
Gilbert of Glockenspur:
Oh, sir, you should read my histories. | My humble life is in debt to your exalted prowess your dauntless courage and your superb swift sword You have the poet's gift of exaggeration Sir you should read my histories
